<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-622-530 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 622 530.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 15 1991 n347 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>University: RISC is best. (Purdue University,reduced-instruction-set computers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Korzeniowski, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Purdue University will begin replacing its NetWare-based serverswith an IBM RS/6000 workstation in May 1991, a dramatic change inits PC-local area network strategy.andP;  The change is in response tothe results of a product-performance assessment conducted earlierin 1991, and to the problems encountered by several of its networkmanagers.andP;  The network will be based on the Transmission ControlProtocol/Internet Protocol.andP;  The product-performance evaluationrevealed that the RS/6000 offered several advantages over theNovell 386 server, including superior performance and tighterintegration with the backbone network, as well as being easier tomanage.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   IBM RS/6000 (Workstation) (Business use).andO;Topic:     Colleges and UniversitiesReduced-Instruction-Set ComputersLocal Area NetworksFile ServersWorkstationsNetwork ManagementBackbone NetworksTestingPurdue University.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Future configuration of the campus backbone network. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>